sec.p:
There are several limitations in this study that should be clarified: (1) the relationship between frequency of occurrence (photograph rate at a given site) and animal density remains unclear (
   Carbone et al., 2001; 
   Li et al., 2010, 
   2014; 
   Liu et al., 2013); (2) the effectiveness of different survey methods can vary depending on species, particularly for small mammals and birds; (3) variation in microclimate on different time frames may cause spatial changes in potential distribution (e.g., we only created variables for annual or seasonal population changes) (
   Broennimann et al., 2012; 
   Sedgeley, 2001); (4) obtaining high-resolution environmental variables may create potential bias (
   Wang et al., 2012); (5) modeling limitations (e.g., part of a species’ fundamental niche may not correspond to any combination of environmental variables; species interactions may cause bias) (
   Cruz-Cárdenas et al., 2014; 
   Elith & Leathwick, 2009; 
   Guo et al., 2015; 
   Maiorano et al., 2013); (6) human influence may be important but is difficult to quantify on a local scale.
